A cyclist is riding on a road, and dashed yellow lines are visible on the pavement in the bottom left corner. The front wheel of another bicycle can be seen on the far left edge of the frame, suggesting an overtake.
A cyclist is riding on a road, with two utility poles visible in the distance ahead and to the right. The cyclist appears to be approaching them.
The cyclist is now riding alongside the two utility poles that were previously in the distance. The front wheel of another bicycle is also visible on the far left of the frame.
reasoning:
The correct temporal order is determined by tracking the cyclist's movement past a series of distinct background objects. The camera is moving alongside the cyclist, so objects in the background will appear in the distance and then move past and off-screen to the left.
